docs.lead_paragraph: In a story Nov. 9 about recent racial incidents on U.S. college campuses, The Associated Press reported erroneously that a second man accused of putting a noose around a University of Mississippi statue faces charges. That man was scheduled to plead guilty to an unspecified charge in September, but the hearing didn't happen and the man hasn't been charged, although the case is pending.
